What's a Bot?

A chatbot, or bot, is "a computer program that conducts a conversation via auditory or textual methods."

Bots are your allies in resolving support cases fast. They can prevent cases from being opened and reduce chat duration by helping customers self-direct immediately.

Most importantly, bots can be trained to understand human language through Natural-Language Processing (NLP).

What makes Einstein Bots so smart? Salesforce Einstein and the power of your data in Salesforce!

Can My Bots Sound like My Company?

Every company has a unique voice. What Help Do I Need to Get Botting?

Bot success starts with building the right team and creating a realistic plan for your company.

Engaged Sessions, Bot Billing, and Bot Performance

Use engaged sessions to track bot use against your monthly subscription allowance and measure bot performance.

Einstein Bots Requirements

Finish these chores before having fun with Einstein Bots: event data, intent data, and bot permissions.

Einstein Bots System Limitations

Understand the maximum number of dialogs that can be attached, steps to implement, or the maximum number of versions per bot.

Einstein Bots and Your Data

Einstein Bots includes event data and intent data. Intent data is discussed in Intent Management.

Understanding Bot Permissions

Enable your team to collaborate building Einstein Bots by assigning custom permissions to profiles.

Learn About Einstein Bots Compliance

Bots are compliant with HIPAA, SOC 2, and ISO standards.

Reduce Bias in Einstein Bots

Reduce bias in your bot by revising your script and intent model. Use accessibility best practices and design by channel to create a great bot experience every time.
title: Setting Up and Using Einstein Bots in Service Cloud
